.TH "i3c_master_get_free_addr" 9 "i3c_master_get_free_addr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
i3c_master_get_free_addr \- get a free address on the bus
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" i3c_master_get_free_addr
.BI "(struct i3c_master_controller *master "  ","
.BI "u8 start_addr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "master" 12
I3C master object
.IP "start_addr" 12
where to start searching
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function must be called with the bus lock held in write mode.
.SH "RETURN"
the first free address starting at \fIstart_addr\fP (included) or -ENOMEM
if there's no more address available.
